Motivation¶

Each year approx 7 million users sign up and create their fantasy football team. Making it most widely used platform for its recreational aspect and now due to its popularity it has turned into a business. I have been using it myself for last 4 years with my friends and colleagues.
Alongwith fantasy data, it also has stats of each player and team in English Premier League. I will use the data collectively to determine insightful facts of FPL, compare my team to know how well I performed in each gameweek and what transfers should I make to make my team better.

Move to top

Creating a function to fetch details for given fpl team_id and gameweek number:

In [2]:
def fetch_myteam_gw(teamID, gw):
    url = 'https://fantasy.premierleague.com/api/entry/{}/event/{}/picks/'.format(teamID,gw)
    team = requests.get(url)
    return team.json()

My FPL team id is 1025373, which is embedded in url link of "View Gameweek history" on my https://fantasy.premierleague.com/my-team page:

In [3]:
myteamID = 1025373
In [4]:
mysquads = []
mypoints = []
for x in range(1,39):
    data = fetch_myteam_gw(myteamID,x)
    if "picks"  in data:
        for i in range(0,15):
            data['picks'][i]['gw'] = x ## adding a field for GameWeek number
            mysquads.append(data['picks'][i])
    if "entry_history" in data:
        data['entry_history']['chip'] = "None"
        if data['active_chip'] != None:
            if data['active_chip'] == 'freehit':
                data['entry_history']['chip'] = 'freehit'
            if data['active_chip'] == '3xc':
                data['entry_history']['chip'] = '3xc'
            if data['active_chip'] == 'bboost':
                data['entry_history']['chip'] = 'bboost'
        mypoints.append(data['entry_history'])
mysquads = pd.DataFrame(mysquads)
mypoints = pd.DataFrame(mypoints)

In [13]:
gameweeks = []
if 'events' in fpl:
    for x in fpl['events']:
        if 'chip_plays' in x:
            x['bboost#'] = 0
            x['3xc#'] = 0
            x['wildcard#'] = 0
            x['freehit#'] = 0
            for y in x['chip_plays']:
                if (y['chip_name']=='bboost'):
                    x['bboost#'] = y['num_played']
                if (y['chip_name']=='3xc'):
                    x['3xc#'] = y['num_played']
                if (y['chip_name']=='wildcard'):
                    x['wildcard#'] = y['num_played']
                if (y['chip_name']=='freehit'):
                    x['freehit#'] = y['num_played']
        if 'top_element_info' in x:
            if (x['top_element_info'] == None):
                x['top_element_points'] = 0
            else:
                x['top_element_points'] = x['top_element_info']['points']
        gameweeks.append(x)
    gameweeks_details = pd.DataFrame(gameweeks)
else:
    print('Gameweek data not found')
In [14]:
if 'elements' in fpl:
    players = fpl['elements']
    players = pd.DataFrame(players)
else:
    print('Players data not found')

Pull and Store Historical Data of Players¶

Move to top

Creating a function to fetch details of given player_id:

In [28]:
def fetch_player_hist(player_id):
    url = 'https://fantasy.premierleague.com/api/element-summary/{}/'.format(player_id)
    plyr = requests.get(url)
    return plyr.json()
In [29]:
player_bygw = []
for x in mysquads['element'].unique():
    hist = fetch_player_hist(x)
    for gw in hist['history']:
        player_bygw_row = {}
        player_bygw_row['element'] = x
        player_bygw_row['gw'] = gw['round']
        player_bygw_row['points'] = gw['total_points']
        player_bygw_row['minutes'] = gw['minutes']
        player_bygw.append(player_bygw_row)
myplayer_gw_points = pd.DataFrame(player_bygw)

In [61]:
overall_avg = pd.concat([myplayer_gw_points[myplayer_gw_points['minutes'] != 0].groupby('element')['gw'].count(),
                                                             myplayer_gw_points.groupby('element')['points'].sum(),
                         myplayer_gw_points[myplayer_gw_points['minutes'] != 0].groupby('element')['points'].mean()], 
                        axis =1, join ='inner').reset_index()
overall_avg.columns = ['element','#_gw_played','total_points','avg_points']
